The gender of a noun can often be surmised by looking at the ending of the word:

Masculine nouns&lt;U+2014&gt;often end in -ur, -i, -ll or -nn
Feminine nouns&lt;U+2014&gt;often end in -a, -ing or -un
Neuter nouns&lt;U+2014&gt;if the last letter of the word has an acute accent (&lt;U+00B4&gt;), then the word is usually neuter

Whilst rare, some nouns, such as leikfimi (gymnastics) are not declined at all.
